<p>I have the misfortune to parse JSON data where different naming policies coexist.</p>  <pre><code>{   "camelCaseData" : {     "someField" : 1   },   "snake_case_data" : {     "some_field" : 2   } } </code></pre>  <p>Is it possible to specify naming policy for the whole <code>snakeCaseData</code>? Or another solution that helps to avoid manual annotating of each field by <code>@SerializedName</code>?</p>  <p>Something like the following</p>  <pre><code>class Data {   CamelCaseData camelCaseData;    @GsonNamingPolicy(com.google.gson.FieldNamingPolicy.LOWER_CASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES )   SnakeCaseData snakeCaseData; } </code></pre>